lead_paragraph: The bloc of European centre-right parties stripped Jacek Saryusz-Wolski of his vice presidency of the group on Monday after the Polish politician accepted Warsaw's nomination to run against fellow-Pole Donald Tusk as chair of EU summit meetings.
